32851.title: Wiki
32851.extract: A wiki (/ˈwɪki/ WIK-ee) is a website that provides collaborative modification of its content and structure directly from the web browser.

32864.title: WikiWikiWeb
32864.extract: The WikiWikiWeb is the first ever wiki, or user-editable website.

33164.title: Wiki software
33164.extract: Wiki software (also known as a wiki engine or wiki application) is collaborative software that runs a wiki, which allows users to create and collaboratively edit "pages" or entries via a web browser.

333752.title: Wiki markup
333752.extract: Wiki markup, also known as wikitext language and wikicode, is a lightweight markup language used to write pages at wiki-based websites (such as Wikipedia) that is a simplified/alternative/intermediate to HTML. Its purpose is to be converted by wiki software into HTML, which, in turn, is served to web browsers.

487926.title: List of wiki software
487926.extract: This is a list of notable wiki software applications.

3118940.title: Semantic wiki
3118940.extract: A semantic wiki is a wiki that has an underlying model of the knowledge described in its pages.

3351748.title: Wiki Wiki Shuttle
3351748.extract: The Wiki Wiki Shuttle is a fare-free shuttle bus system at the Honolulu International Airport.

25133016.title: Wiki hosting service
25133016.extract: A wiki hosting service or wiki farm is a server or an array of servers that offer users tools to simplify the creation and development of individual, independent wikis.

34488787.title: The Hidden Wiki
34488787.extract: The Hidden Wiki is the name of several censorship-resistant wikis operating as Tor hidden services that anyone can anonymously edit after registering on the site.
